<subSubSection id="50F80EB85752FF853DFFF93F05C6F8C0" pageId="14" pageNumber="335" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="185D5D335752FF853DFFF93F05C6F8C0" blockId="14.[189,794,1754,1874]" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis id="2A9681215752FF853DFFF93F060BF960" bold="true" box="[189,318,1754,1778]" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">Etymology.</emphasis>
From Greek 
<emphasis id="2A9681215752FF853C94F93F0507F960" box="[470,562,1754,1778]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">Chimero</emphasis>
- mythological figure characterized by a hybrid appearance referring to the combination of characters of two genera (
<taxonomicName id="DFE226B05752FF853FD7F8FF05DDF8A0" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1860" box="[661,744,1818,1842]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Tibraca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2A9681215752FF853FD7F8FF05DDF8A0" box="[661,744,1818,1842]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">Tibraca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DFE226B05752FF853DFFF8DF064AF8C0" authorityName="Benvegnu" authorityYear="1968" box="[189,383,1850,1874]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Paramecocephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2A9681215752FF853DFFF8DF064AF8C0" box="[189,383,1850,1874]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">Paramecocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and - 
<emphasis id="2A9681215752FF853C8EF8DE0534F8C0" box="[460,513,1851,1874]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">coris</emphasis>
, stink bug; masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="50F80EB85752FF853DFFF89F0562F860" pageId="14" pageNumber="335" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="185D5D335752FF853DFFF89F0562F860" blockId="14.[189,794,1914,2034]" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis id="2A9681215752FF853DFFF89F060AF800" bold="true" box="[189,319,1914,1938]" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="DFE226B05752FF853C05F89F06ECF800" authorityName="BARROs &amp; Barão &amp; Grazia" authorityYear="2020" box="[327,473,1914,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Chimerocoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2A9681215752FF853C05F89F06ECF800" box="[327,473,1914,1938]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">Chimerocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the habitus and length of labium similar to 
<taxonomicName id="DFE226B05752FF853CC4F87F057DF820" authorityName="Benvegnu" authorityYear="1968" box="[390,584,1946,1970]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Paramecocephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2A9681215752FF853CC4F87F057DF820" box="[390,584,1946,1970]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">Paramecocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the morphol-ogy of pygophore similar to 
<taxonomicName id="DFE226B05752FF853CADF85F0577F840" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1860" box="[495,578,1978,2002]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Tibraca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2A9681215752FF853CADF85F0577F840" box="[495,578,1978,2002]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">Tibraca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The comparison of these genera is presented in 
<figureCitation id="80D941B65752FF853CABF83F0567F860" box="[489,594,2010,2034]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="32.[189,222,1983,2005]" captionTargetId="figure-352@33.[151,1398,220,1397]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Fig. 19. Comparative figure of Chimerocoris, Paramecocephala and Tibraca. A–C: habitus dorsal (antennomeres and legs not showing due to edition of photo); D–E: head and pronotum; F–G: habitus ventral; H–I: habitus lateral; J–R: male terminalia: J, M, P: dorsal view; K, N, Q: posterior view; L, O, R: ventral view. — (A, D, F, H, J–L): Chimerocoris luridus; (B, I, M–O): Paramecocephala fusca; (C, E, G, P–R): Tibraca exigua. Scale bars:A– C, F– I = 2.0 mm; D–E = 0.5 mm; J–R = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360301/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">Figure 19</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
