<emphasis id="2A9681215752FF853DFFF7FF067AF7A0" bold="true" box="[189,335,2074,2098]" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">Distribution.</emphasis>
Brazil: Rio Grande do Sul (
<figureCitation id="80D941B65752FF853F39F7FF05FFF7A0" box="[635,714,2074,2098]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="28.[189,222,1311,1333]" captionTargetBox="[209,1417,245,1273]" captionTargetId="figure-325@28.[189,1436,219,1296]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Fig. 17. Map of geographical distribution. — Colors: yellow – Chimerocoris luridus sp.n.; purple – Hypanthracos meridionalis; red – Liscocephala fumosa sp.n.; green – Ogmocoris Mayr, 1864; blue – Triunfus gen. n." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4360283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4360283/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="335">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
